sequenceDiagram
    %% <!-- Generated: v0.5 ADR-0034 | 2026-06-30 -->
    title Orchestrated ingest loop — analyze once, retry generate, bounded, propose/sweep (ADR-0034 §4/§6)
    autonumber

    participant O as Orchestrator
    participant P as InferenceProvider (Local/API)
    participant V as WikiPage validator
    participant U as Usage accumulator
    participant FS as Wiki FS
    participant PG as Postgres
    participant R as ops/review.py

    Note over O: max_iter=3, token_budget=60000 (from provider_config, ADR-0009)
    O->>P: analyze(source_text, vault_context)  %% ONCE per run (AQ-v0.2-1)
    P-->>O: Analysis{topics, entities, language, suggested_pages}
    P->>U: add Usage(input, output, cost)

    loop iteration = 1..max_iter  (stop when converged OR iteration==max_iter OR tokens>=budget)
        Note over O: check token_budget BEFORE the call — if accumulated >= budget, stop converged=False
        O->>P: generate(analysis, retrieval_context + augmentation)
        P-->>O: list[WikiPage]
        P->>U: add Usage(input, output, cost)
        O->>V: validate(pages)  %% type∈enum, title, non-empty sources[], lang, content (ADR-0007 §5)
        alt all pages valid
            V-->>O: OK (converged=True)
            O->>FS: write each WikiPage to wiki/ (I1 upsert, I5 frontmatter)
            O->>PG: persist_metadata + parse links (K5) + upsert vector
            O->>PG: _ensure_source_summary + _update_overview (K3/K4 aggregates)
            Note over O: break out of loop
        else invalid (whole batch retried)
            V-->>O: errors[]
            Note over O: augment retrieval_context with validation errors; iteration += 1
        end
    end

    Note over O: if loop ended without converging → converged=False (AC-K2-5)
    O->>U: finalize → total_tokens, total_cost_usd
    O->>PG: INSERT ingest_runs{max_iter_used, total_tokens, total_cost_usd, converged} (I7)
    Note over O: log total_cost_usd; if > $1.00 → WARNING + cost_anomaly=True (ADR-0009)

    %% ── ADR-0034: Post-generation proposal stage (fire-and-forget, never fails ingest) ──
    Note over O,R: Fire-and-forget: pages already written; any exception below is logged + swallowed
    O-)R: propose_reviews(analysis, pages_written, origin_source, vault_id)
    Note over R: Anti-spam gate (ADR-0034 §4.2): skip LLM if content < MIN_CHARS AND pages < MIN_PAGES AND no dangling links AND no unwritten suggested-pages
    alt gate passes: rule-based signals found (dangling links / unwritten suggested-pages)
        R->>PG: read links table for dangling wikilinks (bounded indexed read, I1 — no vault re-scan)
        R->>PG: INSERT review_items (missing-page/duplicate rows) — no LLM call
    end
    alt gate passes AND suggestion/contradiction/confirm judgment needed
        R->>P: propose(analysis_digest + existing_title_list) via resolve_provider_config("ingest") (I6)
        Note over R: ONE call, no loop, no retry; asyncio.wait_for(REVIEW_PROPOSE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS) (I7)
        P-->>R: list[Proposal] (type, proposed_title, proposed_page_type, rationale)
        Note over R: truncate to REVIEW_PROPOSE_MAX_ITEMS (default 8); log cost via UsageAccumulator (I7)
        R->>PG: INSERT review_items rows (status=pending, item_type, proposed_*, rationale, source_page_id)
    else gate fails OR provider timeout/error
        Note over R: emit only rule-based proposals (if any); log WARNING; zero LLM cost
    end

    %% ── ADR-0034: Auto-resolution sweep (fire-and-forget after propose_reviews) ──
    O-)R: sweep_reviews(vault_id)  %% also triggered after each successful Create action
    Note over R: Pass-1 (rule-based, no LLM): bounded read of pending missing-page/duplicate items (cap REVIEW_SWEEP_MAX_ITEMS)
    R->>PG: SELECT pending missing-page/duplicate items (bounded, I1 — uses ix_review_items_vault_proposed_title)
    loop each candidate item (capped)
        R->>PG: lookup pages.title == proposed_title (normalized)
        alt title now exists as a live page
            R->>PG: UPDATE status=auto_resolved, resolution=rule_resolved, reviewed_by=auto-sweep
        end
    end
    alt REVIEW_SWEEP_LLM_ENABLED=true (default)
        Note over R: Pass-2 (conservative LLM): ONE batched call, cap REVIEW_SWEEP_LLM_MAX_ITEMS (default 8)
        R->>P: sweep_judge(remaining_pending_items + vault_title_list) via resolve_provider_config("ingest") (I6)
        Note over R: asyncio.wait_for(REVIEW_SWEEP_TIMEOUT_SECONDS); default-to-keep on ambiguity/timeout (I7)
        P-->>R: per-item verdict: resolve | keep
        Note over R: never auto-resolve confirm items; log cost; UPDATE resolved items → status=auto_resolved, resolution=llm_resolved
    end
